item.title: Ode to Algocracy
item.description: Town square beheadings, powdered wigs and landline phones – although currently regarded as one of the sacred axioms of modern day democracy, the popular vote will ultimately end up in the same bucket as any other obsolete, bizarre or cruel tradition we used to believe was the pinnacle of our civilization. Are two (or multiple) heads really better than one? Does this mythical entity that periodically emerges from us, the society of voters – a collective-unconscious hydra of sorts – really know what’s best?
